# Browser Automation

## Choosing an approach

| Browser | List tabs | Switch/close tabs |
|---------|-----------|-------------------|
| Chromium (Edge, Chrome, Brave) | CDP `GET /json` | CDP `GET /json/activate/{id}` + System Events |
| Safari | JXA `osascript -l JavaScript` | AppleScript `osascript` with window `id` |

Fall back to JXA for Chromium only when no `--remote-debugging-port` is found in `ps`.

## Why CDP over AppleScript for Chromium

`Application("Microsoft Edge")` / `tell application "Microsoft Edge"` resolve to a **single process** chosen by Launch Services. When multiple instances run (e.g. two Edge profiles with separate user-data-dirs), JXA may enumerate tabs from process A while AppleScript targets process B — causing switches to the wrong window.

CDP avoids this: each instance has its own debug port, so listing and switching are scoped to the correct process.

## CDP patterns

- **Discover instances**: parse `ps -eo pid,args` for `--remote-debugging-port=(\d+)`, skip lines containing `--type=` (those are subprocesses).
- **List tabs**: `http://localhost:PORT/json`, filter `type === "page"`.
- **Switch tab**: `http://localhost:PORT/json/activate/TAB_ID`.
- **Bring to front**: `tell application "System Events" to set frontmost of (first process whose unix id is PID) to true`.
- Use Node.js `http` module for HTTP calls (no external deps needed).

## AppleScript pitfalls

- **Never use window index for targeting** — indices are z-order based and shift when other apps (like Raycast) come to front. Use `window id` instead: `first window whose id is N`.
- For bulk closing, close tabs in **descending index** per window to avoid reindexing.

## Adding a new Chromium browser

Any Chromium fork with `--remote-debugging-port` works. Update **both** extensions:

In each of `browser-tab-switcher/src/switch-tab.tsx` and `browser-tab-bulk-close/src/shared.ts`:

1. **`BrowserName` type** — add the new name to the union
2. **`CHROMIUM_BROWSERS` array** — append the new name
3. **`discoverChromiumInstances()`** — add an `else if (line.includes("AppName"))` branch matching the process path
4. **`browserColor()` / `iconForBrowser()`** — add a `case` for the new browser

Build both extensions afterward: `npx @raycast/api build` in each folder.
